name: packing, clay product | packing, clay product | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/840/documentation

The packing and loading process is normalized with an annual production volume of 1'000'000 kg/a and a density of 1'600 m3/kg. The estimated lifespan of the machines is assumed to be 25 years.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]



Includes the process of packing, transportation within the plant and loading of the bags on paletts. The machines used therefore are included in the infrastructure. The waste treatment after use by the end-user and transports of the packing materials are included.

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data are from one company (packing, lime products) in Switzerland and adjusted for clay products.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Assumption that the same process is used as for packing lime products
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: See geography This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography CH. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Measured data of one Swiss plant
